<!-- Privacy Policy Page -->
<div class="policy-hero full-width">
  <div class="policy-hero__inner">
    <p class="policy-hero__eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="policy-hero__heading">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="policy-hero__meta">Effective Date: 1 January 2025 &nbsp;·&nbsp; KingWorX Pty Ltd (ABN pending)</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="policy-body">
  <nav class="policy-toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
    <p class="policy-toc__title">Contents</p>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#p1">Who We Are</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p2">Information We Collect</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p3">How We Use Your Information</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p4">Sharing Your Information</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p5">Cookies & Tracking</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p6">Data Retention</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p7">Your Rights</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p8">Security</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p9">Third-Party Links</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p10">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="#p11">Contact Us</a></li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <div class="policy-content">

    <section id="p1" class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>KingWorX Pty Ltd ("KingWorX", "we", "our", "us") is an Australian company that designs, imports, and sells automotive performance parts via our online store at <strong>kingworx.com.au</strong>. We are committed to protecting the privacy of our customers, visitors, and suppliers in accordance with the <em>Privacy Act 1988 (Cth)</em> and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p2" class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect personal information only to the extent necessary to operate our business and provide our services.</p>
      <h3>2.1 Information You Give Us</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account / Order Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, billing address, shipping address, and payment details when you make a purchase or create an account.</li>
        <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages you send us via contact forms, email, or support channels.</li>
        <li><strong>Newsletter Subscription:</strong> Email address when you subscribe to our mailing list.</li>
        <li><strong>Reviews & Feedback:</strong> Any content you submit as a product review or in a survey.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Device & Browser Data:</strong> IP address, browser type and version, operating system, referring URLs, and pages visited.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Click paths, time on page, search terms used on our store, and session duration.</li>
        <li><strong>Transaction Metadata:</strong> Purchase history, cart activity, and wishlist interactions.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
      <p>We may receive information from payment processors (e.g., Shopify Payments, Afterpay), shipping carriers, and marketing platforms. We handle this information in accordance with this policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p3" class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <div class="policy-table-wrap">
        <table class="policy-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal Basis</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Processing and fulfilling your orders</td><td>Contractual necessity</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Communicating about your order status and shipping</td><td>Contractual necessity</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Providing customer support</td><td>Legitimate interest / Consent</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Sending marketing emails (where you have opted in)</td><td>Consent</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Improving our products, website, and user experience</td><td>Legitimate interest</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Preventing fraud and maintaining security</td><td>Legitimate interest / Legal obligation</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Complying with legal obligations (e.g. tax records)</td><td>Legal obligation</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="p4" class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Sharing Your Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share it only where necessary:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Shopify Inc.:</strong> Our e-commerce platform hosts our store and processes payments. Shopify's privacy policy applies to data processed on their infrastructure.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment Processors:</strong> Stripe, PayPal, Afterpay — for secure payment processing. Card data is handled directly by these processors and is never stored on our systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Shipping & Logistics Partners:</strong> Australia Post, Sendle, and similar carriers receive your name and address to deliver your order.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing Platforms:</strong> If you have opted in to marketing, we may share your email with platforms such as Klaviyo or Mailchimp to send campaigns on our behalf.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> Where we are required by law, court order, or regulatory authority to disclose information.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>All third parties we work with are required to handle your data securely and in accordance with applicable privacy laws.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p5" class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
      <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Keep you logged in and remember your cart contents</li>
        <li>Analyse site traffic and user behaviour (via Google Analytics)</li>
        <li>Deliver relevant advertising on other platforms (e.g. Meta Pixel, Google Ads)</li>
        <li>Measure the performance of our marketing campaigns</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can control cookies via your browser settings. Disabling certain cookies may affect site functionality such as persistent cart or login sessions. Where required by law, we will seek your consent before placing non-essential cookies.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p6" class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer period is required by law. Specifically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Order records:</strong> 7 years (Australian tax law requirement)</li>
        <li><strong>Customer accounts:</strong> Until account deletion is requested</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing consent records:</strong> 3 years from last interaction</li>
        <li><strong>Support communications:</strong> 2 years from resolution</li>
      </ul>
      <p>When your data is no longer required, we securely delete or anonymise it.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p7" class="policy-section">
      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under the Australian Privacy Principles, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal information we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate or outdated information</li>
        <li><strong>Request deletion</strong> of your data (subject to legal retention obligations)</li>
        <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of marketing communications at any time via the unsubscribe link in our emails</li>
        <li><strong>Lodge a complaint</strong> with the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC) at <em>oaic.gov.au</em></li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise your rights, contact us at <strong>privacy@kingworx.com.au</strong>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p8" class="policy-section">
      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>SSL/TLS encryption on all data transmission</li>
        <li>PCI-DSS compliant payment processing (via Shopify Payments)</li>
        <li>Access controls limiting who within KingWorX can access your data</li>
        <li>Regular review of our data-handling practices</li>
      </ul>
      <p>No system is 100% secure. If you believe your account has been compromised, contact us immediately at <strong>support@kingworx.com.au</strong>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p9" class="policy-section">
      <h2>9. Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>Our website may link to third-party websites (e.g., brands we stock, review platforms). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p10" class="policy-section">
      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the effective date at the top of this page. For significant changes, we may notify you via email or a notice on our website. Continued use of our site after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="p11" class="policy-section">
      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions or concerns about your privacy or this policy, please contact us:</p>
      <div class="policy-contact-box">
        <p><strong>KingWorX Pty Ltd</strong><br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@kingworx.com.au">privacy@kingworx.com.au</a><br>
        Website: <a href="/pages/contact">kingworx.com.au/pages/contact</a><br>
        Response time: Within 5 business days</p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>

